                    "company": "Het Nieuwe Instituut",
                    "description": "The R&D department acknowledges and gives visibility to research projects, practices, and initiatives,\nwhose success is understood in their ability to offer departures from established modes of thinking.\nGrounded in the principles of design and innovation, concepts bound up with optimism as well as change\nand inherent conflicts, the investigations, exhibitions, and public events aim to become a motor for collective forms of knowledge and alternative forms of living. The department connects research projects\nwith the existing collection of The State Archive of Dutch Architecture through a series of archive\nexplorations. This endeavour not only acknowledges gaps (both thematic and methodological) in the\nofficial historiography \u2014 such as feminisms in architecture, queer perspectives, collective and\nradically improvisational spatial practices, as well as the architectural legacy of the former Dutch colonial\nterritories\u2014 but also works to reframe acquisition policies to include new documents, subjects, and\nmedia.\nOtero, as founding director of the department, launched the first HNI International Open Call for\nFellows; initiated the Reading Room Conference Series; and directed, among others, the projects \u2018Automated Landscapes,\u2019 focusing on the emerging architectures of automated labour; \u2018Architecture of Appropriation,\u2019 on squatting as spatial practice; and \u201cArchitectures of Security,\u201d a critical research on urban security and the consequences of the increasing militarization of public space.",
                    "title": "Director of Research",
                    "employment_type": "Full-time"
                }
            ]
